BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:wM__rZxyC5cUEraMkI347
SUMMARY:South Lynnwood Park Stewardship Event
DTSTAMP:20260308T004820Z
DTSTART:20260321T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:City of Lynnwood Parks welcomes volunteers of all abilities who
	 want to contribute to the restoration and conservation of our parks in So
	uth Lynnwood Neighborhood. The goal of each event is to provide a safe\, e
	njoyable\, and effective hands-on experience for you to help improve the h
	ealth of your urban parks. These monthly events\, which will be held on th
	e third weekend of each month\, will involve removing invasive plants\, he
	lp with restoration plantings\, and picking up garbage. Events are 100% ou
	tdoors and will generally be held ‘rain or shine’ but may be canceled or r
	elocated if weather or site conditions are unsafe such as high winds\, flo
	oding\, snow\, lightning\, or unsafe air quality \\(smoke\\).\n\nhttps://s
	eatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/south-lynnwood-park-stewardship-event
	/18215110/2026-03-21T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/south-lynnwood-park-stewa
	rdship-event/18215110/2026-03-21T00
LOCATION:Scriber Lake Park\, 5562 196th St SW\, Lynnwood\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7w2Dhe9Iz163j2NBVth-L
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Upper Luther Burbank Park
DTSTAMP:20260308T004820Z
DTSTART:20260321T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a Clean-up in Upper Luther Burbank Park \n\nCome  e
	xplore Upper Luther Burbank Park\, a wonderful\, forested park with large 
	trees\, a steep ravine\, and fun trails to explore. We will be working in 
	the park to help remove ivy from the understory. It will be a great chanc 
	e to get your hands in the dirt\, learn about native plants and our local 
	forests\, and work alongside neighbors and friends!\n\nNo experience neces
	sary\, all ages welcome\; gloves and tools are provided. \n\nPlease note: 
	we require participants aged 14 and under to volunteer with a parent o r g
	uardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen: Saturday\, March 21st\, 
	10am-1pm\n\nWhere: Upper Luther Burbank Park\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for t
	he weather in clothes you don't mind getting dirty \\(think: long pants\, 
	boots or sneakers\\). Bring a water bottle. Small snacks\, gloves\, and to
	ols will be provided.\n\nRegistration: volunteersignup.org/CTFM7\n\nhttps:
	//seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-upper-luther-bur
	bank-park/18066406/2026-03-21T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-upper-l
	uther-burbank-park/18066406/2026-03-21T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
